cs.CV, cs.MED, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI

The paper deals with the problem of automatic detection of anatomical landmarks in X-ray images, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the application of the proposed method to pelvic trauma surgery, which falls under the medical imaging domain, making cs.MED (Medical Imaging) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of X-ray image guidance for percutaneous alternatives to complex procedures, which involves robotics and automation, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category. The paper proposes a sequential prediction framework based on convolutional layers, which is a deep learning approach, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of pre-operative CT and image-based 2D/3D registration, which involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
